        "incorrect": {
          "Repeating the same phrase over and over": "This describes perseveration or echolalia (repeating others' words), not clanging. Clanging specifically involves rhyming patterns connecting different words in a chain, not repetition of the same content.",
          "Speaking extremely slowly with long pauses": "This describes poverty of speech (alogia) or psychomotor slowing, which are negative symptoms. Clanging is actually often rapid - the words flow quickly because sound associations trigger each next word automatically.",
          "Using made-up words that have no meaning": "This describes neologisms (creating new words). Clanging uses REAL words - they just happen to rhyme with each other instead of forming coherent thoughts. The words themselves are recognizable; their combination doesn't make sense."
