          "Schizophrenia": "Schizophrenia requires functional decline - the person typically cannot work, maintain relationships, or care for themselves properly. This man works full-time as a bus driver. Also, schizophrenia usually involves multiple symptom types (hallucinations, disorganized speech, negative symptoms) - he only has delusions.",
          "Schizophreniform disorder": "Schizophreniform has the same symptoms as schizophrenia (multiple psychotic symptom types, functional impairment) but shorter duration. This man has ONLY delusions, preserved functioning, and no other symptoms - the symptom picture doesn't match schizophreniform regardless of duration.",
          "Brief psychotic disorder": "Brief psychotic disorder requires symptoms to last less than 1 month. The scenario implies this has been ongoing (multiple police reports, covering walls). Also, brief psychotic typically involves full resolution, not ongoing symptoms."
