      }
    },
    {
      "question": "A 24-year-old student experiences sudden onset of paranoid delusions (FBI surveillance, classmates poisoning her) after failing exams and having a major argument. She is terrified, barely sleeps for 5 days, and screams at 'agents.' After 12 days of treatment, symptoms completely resolve and she returns to normal with full insight. What diagnosis best fits?",
      "difficulty": "application",
