        "correct": "This is schizoaffective disorder. The patient has: (1) Psychotic symptoms - auditory hallucinations and persecutory delusions lasting 2 years, meeting schizophrenia criteria, AND (2) Major mood episodes - both depressive episodes AND elevated mood periods (suggesting manic features). Schizoaffective requires BOTH psychotic symptoms AND major mood episodes. The 2-year duration and presence of both depression and mania alongside continuous psychosis points clearly to schizoaffective.",
        "incorrect": {
          "Schizophrenia": "Schizophrenia does NOT include prominent mood episodes. This patient has recurrent major depressive episodes AND elevated mood periods - these are not minor mood fluctuations but significant mood disturbances. When psychosis + major mood episodes both occur, schizoaffective is the diagnosis.",
